type Language string

const (
	French    Language = "french"
	Italian   Language = "italian"
	Spanish   Language = "spanish"
	Hindi     Language = "hindi"
	Bulgarian Language = "bulgarian"
	Serbian   Language = "serbian"
)

// GetGreeting generates a greeting in
// the specified language
func GetGreeting(language Language) string {
	switch language {
	case French:
		return "Bonjour"
	case Italian:
		return "Ciao"
	case Spanish:
		return "Hola"
	case Hindi:
		return ""
	case Bulgarian:
		return ""
	case Serbian:
		return ""
	default:
		return "Hello"
	}
}

files.body:
package voting

import (
	"strings"
	"testing"
	"time"

	"std"

	"gno.land/p/nt/testutils"
	"gno.land/p/nt/uassert"
	"gno.land/p/nt/ufmt"
)

// create helper - make proposal and return its id
func mustCreateProposal(t *testing.T, author string, text string, mins int) string {
	addr := testutils.TestAddress(author)
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(addr))

	id, err := CreateProposal(cross, text, mins)
	uassert.True(t, err == nil, "CreateProposal err="+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))
	uassert.True(t, id != "", "expected non-empty id")
	return id
}

func TestCreateProposalAndRenderIndex(t *testing.T) {
	text := "Dodati dark mode u Voting dApp"
	author := "alya"

	id := mustCreateProposal(t, author, text, 60)

	// Render
	got := Render("")
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(got, text), "list render should contain text")
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(got, id), "list render should contain id")

	// Render details
	got = Render("id/" + id)
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(got, text), "detail render should contain text")
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(got, "Proposal #"), "detail render should have title")
}

func TestVoteYesNo(t *testing.T) {
	id := mustCreateProposal(t, "alice", "Feature X", 30)

	// Bob votes YES
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("bob")))
	err := Vote(cross, id, true)
	uassert.True(t, err == nil, "bob vote err="+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))

	// Charlie votes NO
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("charlie")))
	err = Vote(cross, id, false)
	uassert.True(t, err == nil, "charlie vote err="+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))

	yes, no, closed := GetResult(id)
	uassert.Equal(t, 1, yes)
	uassert.Equal(t, 1, no)
	uassert.False(t, closed, "proposal should still be open")
} // <-- nedostajala vitiasta

func TestDoubleVoteRejected(t *testing.T) {
	id := mustCreateProposal(t, "alice", "sth new", 20)

	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("dave")))
	err := Vote(cross, id, true)
	uassert.True(t, err == nil, "first vote should succeed, err="+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))

	// try to vote again
	err = Vote(cross, id, false)
	uassert.True(t, err == ErrAlreadyVoted, "expected ErrAlreadyVoted, got "+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))
}

func TestVotingClosed(t *testing.T) {
	id := mustCreateProposal(t, "alice", "Kratak test", 10)

	// manually close proposal
	raw, ok := proposals.Get(id)
	uassert.True(t, ok, "proposal not found")
	prop := raw.(*Proposal)
	prop.Deadline = time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Minute) // in the past

	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("erin")))
	err := Vote(cross, id, true)
	uassert.True(t, err == ErrVotingClosed, "expected ErrVotingClosed, got "+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))
}

func TestRenderShowsResults(t *testing.T) {
	id := mustCreateProposal(t, "alice", "UI improvments", 30)

	// one vote YES, one vote NO
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("bob")))
	_ = Vote(cross, id, true)
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("charlie")))
	_ = Vote(cross, id, false)

	page := Render("id/" + id)
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(page, "YES = 1"), "detail should show YES=1")
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(page, "NO = 1"), "detail should show NO=1")
}

files.body:
package voting

import (
	"strings"
	"testing"
	"time"

	"std"

	"gno.land/p/nt/testutils"
	"gno.land/p/nt/uassert"
	"gno.land/p/nt/ufmt"
)

// create helper - make proposal and return its id
func mustCreateProposal(t *testing.T, author string, text string, mins int) string {
	addr := testutils.TestAddress(author)
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(addr))

	id, err := CreateProposal(cross, text, mins)
	uassert.True(t, err == nil, "CreateProposal err="+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))
	uassert.True(t, id != "", "expected non-empty id")
	return id
}

func TestCreateProposalAndRenderIndex(t *testing.T) {
	text := "Dodati dark mode u Voting dApp"
	author := "alya"

	id := mustCreateProposal(t, author, text, 60)

	// Render
	got := Render("")
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(got, text), "list render should contain text")
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(got, id), "list render should contain id")

	// Render details
	got = Render("id/" + id)
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(got, text), "detail render should contain text")
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(got, "Proposal #"), "detail render should have title")
}

func TestVoteYesNo(t *testing.T) {
	id := mustCreateProposal(t, "alice", "Feature X", 30)

	// Bob votes YES
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("bob")))
	err := Vote(cross, id, true)
	uassert.True(t, err == nil, "bob vote err="+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))

	// Charlie votes NO
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("charlie")))
	err = Vote(cross, id, false)
	uassert.True(t, err == nil, "charlie vote err="+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))

	yes, no, closed := GetResult(id)
	uassert.Equal(t, 1, yes)
	uassert.Equal(t, 1, no)
	uassert.False(t, closed, "proposal should still be open")
} // <-- nedostajala vitiasta

func TestDoubleVoteRejected(t *testing.T) {
	id := mustCreateProposal(t, "alice", "sth new", 20)

	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("dave")))
	err := Vote(cross, id, true)
	uassert.True(t, err == nil, "first vote should succeed, err="+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))

	// try to vote again
	err = Vote(cross, id, false)
	uassert.True(t, err == ErrAlreadyVoted, "expected ErrAlreadyVoted, got "+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))
}

func TestVotingClosed(t *testing.T) {
	id := mustCreateProposal(t, "alice", "Kratak test", 10)

	// manually close proposal
	raw, ok := proposals.Get(id)
	uassert.True(t, ok, "proposal not found")
	prop := raw.(*Proposal)
	prop.Deadline = time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Minute) // in the past

	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("erin")))
	err := Vote(cross, id, true)
	uassert.True(t, err == ErrVotingClosed, "expected ErrVotingClosed, got "+ufmt.Sprintf("%v", err))
}

func TestRenderShowsResults(t *testing.T) {
	id := mustCreateProposal(t, "alice", "UI improvments", 30)

	// one vote YES, one vote NO
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("bob")))
	_ = Vote(cross, id, true)
	testing.SetRealm(std.NewUserRealm(testutils.TestAddress("charlie")))
	_ = Vote(cross, id, false)

	page := Render("id/" + id)
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(page, "YES = 1"), "detail should show YES=1")
	uassert.True(t, strings.Contains(page, "NO = 1"), "detail should show NO=1")
}

package runtime

type Language string

const (
	French    Language = "french"
	Italian   Language = "italian"
	Spanish   Language = "spanish"
	Hindi     Language = "hindi"
	Bulgarian Language = "bulgarian"
	Serbian   Language = "serbian"
)

// GetGreeting generates a greeting in
// the specified language
func GetGreeting(language Language) string {
	switch language {
	case French:
		return "Bonjour"
	case Italian:
		return "Ciao"
	case Spanish:
		return "Hola"
	case Hindi:
		return ""
	case Bulgarian:
		return ""
	case Serbian:
		return ""
	default:
		return "Hello"
	}
}
